17" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569817"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What Are the Benefits of Using Functional Fitness Gloves?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680885933724" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680885933724" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Here are some of the benefits of using fitness workout gloves:&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506608137" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670506608137"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Injury Prevention&nbsp;</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764626941" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673764626941" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Fitness lifting gloves are designed to provide hand protection by putting a durable material between the barbell and your hands. This helps to prevent <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/corns-and-calluses/symptoms-causes/syc-20355946" class="" target="_blank">calluses</a>, blisters, and skin irritation caused by repeated contact.</p><p>Gloves with wrist support also help to reduce wrist stress, therefore reducing the chance of injury.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569822" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670485569822"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Enhances Grip</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670485569821" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670485569821" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Most hand grips and gloves have a grippy inside layer that helps to keep contact with the bar, therefore reducing the chance of your grip slipping or grip fatigue.</p><p>The straps and wrist support help to reduce the grip pressure, therefore enhancing your grip.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701392928355" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701392928355" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701392928345" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701392928345" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701392928383" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1701392928383"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701392928265" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701392928265" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701392928324" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701392928324"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">Functional fitness gloves offer a great addition to your fitness accessory bag and provide excellent hand protection and comfort. The 7 glove choices I’ve reviewed above feature a range of unique designs which make them suited for a wide range of athlete needs and goals.</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1701392928387" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1701392928387" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564763470" data-id="1686564763470"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701392928348" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1701392928348" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" target="_blank"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fc0a1a19-2e31-4fa8-a43b-9c408a123923/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Oleksiy.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="531" height="533" data-width="20%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="531" natural-height="533"></a></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564765807" data-id="1686564765807"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701392928288" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701392928288"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1701392928358" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1701392928358"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672895064923" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1672895064923"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Hygiene&nbsp;</span></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672895061465" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1672895061465" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Let’s face it: high-intensity exercise causes you to sweat, breathe heavily, and even bleed sometimes. The last thing some people want is to touch a surface that’s not been cleaned properly.</p><p>Wearing gloves helps to provide comfort and some added hygiene protection over bare hands.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764710691" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673764710691"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>When Do You Need Functional Fitness Gloves?</strong></span></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673764700638" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673764700638" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Functional fitness gloves offer a range of versatile uses that cater to a wide range of athlete abilities and needs. These include:</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680886666683" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680886666683" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p></p><ul><li>Any level of cross fitter struggling with skin irritation which includes scuffs, scratches, calluses, and blisters</li><li>Beginner athletes who are new to lifting and therefore more prone to skin irritation</li><li>Lifters who suffer from wrist injuries or pain that need additional support when lifting</li><li>Lifters who struggle to keep a strong bar grip and are looking for extra performance support</li><li>People who prefer to limit exercise equipment contact using their bare hands</li><li>Elite level cross fitters looking for an extra level of performance</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781715573" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675781715573" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/464d83e8-6244-4664-8e9f-ef718b253eb8/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/functional-fitness-grips-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="functional fitness grips" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="functional fitness grips" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506766447" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670506766447"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What To Look For in the Best Functional Fitness Gloves</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680886734185" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680886734185" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>When deciding on a suitable pair of cross training gloves to purchase, consider the following factors:</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675081935903" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675081935903"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Construction/Design</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675081937983" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675081937983" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Different glove design features include the number of finger holes, closure mechanism, and amount of finger coverage.</p><p>Different types of gloves can include normal gloves, grips, and <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-wrist-wraps-for-lifting" class="" target="_blank">wrist wraps</a>, all of which change the most suitable use and benefits.</p><p>Concerning the number of finger holes, consider the amount of finger coverage needed. If you struggle with calluses, a fuller glove design may be a better choice. If you want extra grip but don’t need callus protection, go with a more minimal design.</p><p>If you’re using the gloves or grips for lots of high-volume fitness work, go for a pair that has a durable closure mechanism such as a wrap-around Velcro strap or hook and loop mechanism.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781843365" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781843365"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Materials&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680886814024" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680886814024" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The type of material used in the functional fitness gloves changes the performance therefore it’s good to be aware of the most common materials when choosing.</p><p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leather" class="" target="_blank">Leather </a>is most commonly used and offers high-quality grip and flexibility which allow the gloves to mold well as you wear them.</p><p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neoprene" class="" target="_blank">Neoprene </a>is great for breathability, comfort, and is easy to wash. However, it doesn’t give the same durability as leather.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787081135" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1675787081135" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/65824487-5360-4b7e-bd17-38fd580e090c/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-training-in-gym-with-functional-fitness-grips.jpg" alt="athlete training in gym with functional fitness grips" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete training in gym with functional fitness grips" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675781867139" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675781867139"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Fit</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680886886105" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680886886105" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Fit is perhaps one of the most important and overlooked factors when choosing the correct pair. If your gloves don’t fit correctly, they can’t perform their function correctly.</p><p>Make sure your gloves are tight enough so they don’t fall off during exercise but not too tight so they reduce blood flow or hand movement.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787155402" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787155402"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Support&nbsp;</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680886989560" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680886989560" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Built-in glove support includes hand padding and wrist support, both of which can help to enhance functional fitness performance.</p><p>If you’re struggling with hand comfort when lifting, gloves that offer additional padding may be a good choice. If you need additional <a href="https://gripads.com/blog/wrist-support-wraps/#:~:text=A%20wrist%20wrap%20provides%20additional,you're%20looking%20to%20strengthen." class="" target="_blank">wrist support when lifting</a> or feel like you lift better with added protection, go with gloves with built-in wrist support.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787440275" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787440275"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787464047" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787464047"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Should I Wear Gloves for Functional Fitness?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109356404" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109356404"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Due to the high-volume nature of functional fitness, hand blisters and skin abrasions may be common, especially when starting. The use of functional fitness gloves may be warranted for hand protection during normal training if your hands are currently damaged, or if you simply prefer wearing them.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787889767" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787889767"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Why Do Functional Fitness Athletes Tape Their Fingers?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109396634" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109396634"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Functional fitness athletes tape their hands, more specifically their thumbs to protect them from <a href="https://www.healthdirect.gov.au/blisters" class="" target="_blank">blisters </a>and stop them from slipping when using a hook grip. Applying tape to fingers or thumbs takes seconds and is easy with practice.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675787928690" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1675787928690"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Should Gym Gloves Be Tight or Loose?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1678109395905" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1678109395905"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Gym gloves should be well fitting so that they don’t fall off the hands but not too tight so that they restrict blood flow. If your gloves slip during training, they are too loose. If you notice changes in skin color when wearing them, they are likely too tight.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1684796543928" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1684796543928" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context": "https://schema.org","@type": "FAQPage","mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question","name": "Should I Wear Gloves for functional fitness?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Due to the high-volume nature of functional fitness, hand blisters and skin abrasions may be common, especially when starting. The use of functional fitness gloves may be warranted for hand protection during normal training if your hands are currently damaged, or if you simply prefer wearing them."}},{"@type": "Question","name": "Why Do functional fitness athletes Tape Their Fingers?","acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer","text": "Functional fitness athletes tape their hands, more specifically their thumbs to protect them from blisters and stop them from slipping when using a hook grip. Applying tape to fingers or thumbs takes seconds and is easy with practice."}},{"@type": "Question","name": "Should Gym Gloves Be Tight or L